It's time to tear up our bedroom. The last room in the house that hasn't been touched except for a bit of decorating.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the fireplace hearth have to go. We need to build up the fireplace, replace the cracked plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dry :(
All set for the stucco artist next week
The small side niche turned out well
A new wardrobe is coming in here (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought about installing this nice little vent flap so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there🪺
The stucco artist is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlayment is in place, I made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Floor parts are finished and can be laid. We're currently having tea break
Buhu. Today progress is slow because of super complicated cuts around the door posts, so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Finished, but at the end! The climax was the terrible installation instructions for the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator comes in a month, so we currently have raw plaster style
A little DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel out the lower sections around the door posts, where the floor should fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
We finished the floor in the hallway yesterday! Then at 5 a.m. we went out to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a little nap and a final sprint in the hallway, the baseboards are installed. The joints will be made once the glue is dry
